Trinkler, "Thermal Effects in Relation to Ammunition Storage", 1958
column20: An ebonite lacquer applied to an aluminium plate was used for radiation measurement. The radiation density was determined on the basis of the amount of melted varnish. Wind strengths between 3-10 m/s were measured during the experiments, resulting in relatively large scattering of the results in the various measurement directions. In reference, no individual values for duration are provided, only relationship t=0.93Q^0.21 (NB average flux calculated from flux density and burn duration; peak flux calculated as 2.65 x average flux)
